Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle the @smoked paprika{1%sachet}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

When the chips are halfway through baking, heat a large #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{} on medium-high heat. Add the @slow cooked beef{280%grams} along with the juices from the packet.

Simmer on low with the lid on until tender enough to shred with a #fork{}, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the beef is piping hot throughout.

While the beef simmers, in a medium #bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} and toss to evenly coat. Set aside to pickle.

Once the beef is tender, remove the lid and shred the meat. Stir in the @BBQ sauce{64%grams}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat. Cover to keep warm.

Halve the @burger buns{2} and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} (see pantry for amount) over the bun lids.

Top the bun bases with the pulled beef and some of the slaw, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve with the paprika chips and any remaining slaw on the side. Enjoy!